HEADWORD: Gastroelytrotomy
<hw>Gas`tro*el`y*trot"o*my</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Gastro-</ets> + Gr <?/ sheath + <?/ a cutting]</ety>
<fld>(Surg.)</fld> <def>The operation of cutting into the upper part of
the vagina, through the abdomen (without opening the peritoneum), for
the purpose of removing a fetus. It is a substitute for the C⟦ae⟧sarean
operation, and less dangerous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

